      <article language="en">
        <title locale="en_US">Sex attractant, distribution and DNA barcodes for the Afrotropical leaf-mining moth &lt;i&gt;Phyllonorycter melanosparta &lt;/i&gt;(Lepidoptera: Gracillariidae)</title>
        <abstract locale="en_US">The sex attractant for &lt;i&gt;Phyllonorycter&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;melanosparta&lt;/i&gt; (Meyrick, 1912) has been determined as (10E)-dodec-10-en-1-yl acetate and (10E)-dodec-10-en-1-ol combined in a ratio 10:1. The distribution of this species in Eastern Africa is updated and its presence in Kenya is recorded for the first time. We discuss the taxonomic status of &lt;i&gt;P.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;melanosparta&lt;/i&gt; with reference to three character sets: semiochemicals, morphological and molecular characters (DNA barcodes). This combination of characters is also proposed as a new approach to study the diversity and phylogeny of &lt;i&gt;Phyllonorycter&lt;/i&gt; in the Afrotropical region.</abstract>
